The paper proposes a new model for knowledge graph completion using deep learning techniques, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The model also involves the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) to model sequences, which is a common technique in natural language processing (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper deals with knowledge graphs, which are a type of database (cs.DB).
